testcase.name: Podam should fill values invoking children setters accepting a type different from the parent type
Invoking Podam on a POJO with a private, no arguments constructor, should return a non null POJO
Invoking Podam on a POJO with a circular constructor (e.g. java.net.URL) leads to a null POJO
Podam should fill POJOs with public, non default constructors
Podam should fill embedded abstract classes if a concrete type has been specified
Podam should fill POJOs with protected, non default constructors
Podam should return a null value for non instantiable POJOs
Podam should generate a non null POJO for Abstract types with a concrete type
Podam should handle POJOs with self reference constructors but not default constructors without the need for the @PodamConstructor annotation
Podam should throw an exception if a POJO contains invalid getters or setters
Podam should handle POJOs with private constructors only
Invoking Podam on a POJO with both circular and non circular constructors (e.g. javax.activation.DataHandler) should lead to a non empty POJO
